<em>What is the internet?</em><br>
The world wide web is a collection of <b>HTML</b><br>
World wide web = collection of documents
HTML = documents = hypertext markup language.
<br><br>
Users access the internet through their <b>browser</b> (examples: Safari, Chrome, Firefox etc...)<br>
The browser accesses a website by entering the <b>URL</b> which is the website (example: google.com)<br>
The users browser sends the <b>HTTP</b> request to the <b>server</b> which is storing the website as an HTML<br>
The browser reads the HTML documents and displays it for the user.<br>
<br>
<em>Explain HTML</em><br>
HTML documents are made of <b>HTML elements.</b><br>
Elements are grouped into <b>inline</b> and <b>block.</b><br>
It's important to remember block elements act as if an invisible box is around them.<br>
<br>
To create a hyperlink, use the "a" tag, for example:<br>
<a href="www.the-url.com">The text you want to display</a> <br>
To create image an image use the "img" tag, for example:<br>
<img src=“url” alt=“text”><br>
URLS = addresses
<br><br>

Your instructions to the computer must use perfect syntax for it to interpret them correctly.
